[SN]TITLE[SN]
Belgian biker seriously hurt in Highlands crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Belgian biker is in a serious condition in hospital following a crash in the Highlands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 55-year-old man was part of a group travelling around the north of Scotland.
He was airlifted to hospital with serious injuries after the collision with a blue Mazda 6 car on the A87 near the Cluanie Inn at Glenmoriston at about 16:50 on Saturday.
The driver and passenger in the car were not hurt.
A Police Scotland spokesman said: "Police Scotland can confirm a motorcyclist is being treated for serious injuries in hospital following a two-vehicle collision on the A87 near the Cluanie Inn.
"Inquiries are being carried out by officers from the Road Policing Unit in Fort William, and they are appealing for any witnesses who have not already been spoken to by police to contact them."
